1
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:32,560
Your father will be out soon.

2
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:35,380
Really?

3
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:36,000
Yes.

4
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:37,340
In a couple of days.

5
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:38,720
He's been on good behavior,

6
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:40,520
so they're releasing him early.

7
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:43,640
When will my dad

8
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:45,400
and mom get divorced?

9
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:49,600
Ask him when he gets out.

10
00:01:52,039 --> 00:01:52,720
Uncle,

11
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:56,759
why do you look so tired?

12
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:00,080
I...

13
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,760
I miss your grandmother.

14
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:08,919
I miss my grandma too.

15
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,160
Don't cry.

16
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:35,760
Uncle.

17
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,620
I want to see the train.

18
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,400
I always dream

19
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:57,000
that my mom and dad

20
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:00,080
are coming back on a train.

21
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,560
School's out.

22
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:24,800
Dad, why are you home so early today?

23
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:25,920
I'm not busy today.

24
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:27,780
Come here and watch the Olympics.

25
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,280
I think you, Mengmeng,

26
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,400
should do rhythmic gymnastics in the future.

27
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,520
You already have dance training.

28
00:04:36,520 --> 00:04:37,360
If you train in rhythmic gymnastics,

29
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,280
you could win a gold medal

30
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:40,640
at the Olympics and bring glory to our country.

31
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:41,440
Sounds good.

32
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:41,960
Right?

33
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:43,720
What should my brother train in?

34
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,159
He's not good for training.

35
00:04:45,159 --> 00:04:47,480
The Olympics doesn't have eating competitions.

36
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:49,920
I think with his build,

37
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:50,850
he could do judo.

38
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:53,440
Many judo athletes have his body type.

39
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:54,370
Would you train?

40
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,480
Do you have a lot of homework?

41
00:04:58,480 --> 00:04:59,240
Not much.

42
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:00,760
A lot.

43
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:03,280
Do you want to do it first?

44
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,480
I don't want to watch TV.

45
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:06,040
What are you going to do?

46
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:06,800
Watch with me or do homework?

47
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,530
Watch first.

48
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,240
Alright.

49
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,440
I think Mengmeng

50
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:24,840
will respect me less and less in the future.

51
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,200
She is

52
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,050
quite troublesome.

53
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:35,920
Otherwise,

54
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:39,400
I'm thinking we should have another child.

55
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:40,400
After it's born,

56
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:41,720
we can use the younger one to scare the older one.

57
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,720
What do you think?

58
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:46,200
If you want another baby, go have it with someone else.

59
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:47,360
Besides,

60
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:49,980
does it need to be so complicated?

61
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,570
Isn't it necessary?

62
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:57,600
I'll beat you up in front of her.

63
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,200
Let's see if that scares her.

64
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:01,560
That's really impressive.

65
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:03,220
She'll definitely be scared.

66
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:04,120
What are you talking about?

67
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:04,720
This is...

68
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:09,380
We already have two kids and you don't think that's enough?

69
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,360
In a few days,

70
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,760
Erpang's father will be back,

71
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:19,560
and he'll go back to his own home.

72
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:21,560
Does he have a place to stay when he returns?

73
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,290
Does he have a home to go back to?

74
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:28,780
Let me tell you something.

75
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,200
I...

76
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:34,800
I'll have to work night shifts in a few days.

77
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:37,240
Why do you need to work night shifts?

78
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:38,240
The factory requires it.

79
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,700
There's no 'why' about it.

80
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:42,680
Will you get extra pay for night shifts?

81
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:45,010
Of course there will be compensation.

82
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,440
How much will they pay?

83
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:49,240
Each day, probably...

84
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,930
about 100 yuan, I guess.

85
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:52,480
Would they really pay that much?

86
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:53,360
Working day and night like that,

87
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,800
they have to pay for it.

88
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:03,320
Mom's hospital fees,

89
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,200
can we get the deposit back now?

90
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:06,460
Yes, we can get it back.

91
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,280
Then go get it tomorrow.

92
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:08,880
I'll go

93
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:10,160
when I have time.

94
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,400
It's several thousand yuan.

95
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,240
Yes, I know.

96
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:19,040
Okay, I got it.

97
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:21,720
Do this. Find someone to set it up first.

98
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:23,080
If they can't figure it out, I'll come over.

99
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:23,800
Alright.

100
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:26,760
I must be busy with something right now.

101
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,200
Fine.

102
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,040
Got it.

103
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,720
I'll go right away.

104
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:31,920
I'll be there in 30 minutes.

105
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:32,920
Brother.

106
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:33,840
If there's something urgent over there,

107
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:34,720
you should go first.

108
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,840
We can wait here.

109
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:38,240
No matter how urgent that is,

110
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,900
it's not as important as this.

111
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:42,240
Brother.

112
00:07:43,159 --> 00:07:44,920
You're just too sentimental.

113
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:46,560
Huo Dongfeng has been

114
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,480
locked up for over ten years.

115
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:49,010
What can he possibly do now?

116
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:52,370
Although he was once one of the Three Heroes of Dalin,

117
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:53,720
in today's society,

118
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:56,120
who's going to respect him when he gets out?

119
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:58,200
Let me tell you about the other two heroes,

120
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,600
then you'll understand.

121
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,240
One of them is at the school gate

122
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:02,320
popping popcorn.

123
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:04,680
Making noise with his popper all day.

124
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,800
And the other one peddles a cart.

125
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,560
Acting all tough,

126
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:09,620
pedaling that cart faster than a car.

127
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:11,840
Is that funny?

128
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,960
What's wrong with popping popcorn?

129
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:21,440
What's wrong with pedaling a cart?

130
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:23,440
It means they're doing honest work.

131
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,260
Not getting into trouble.

132
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:28,200
Let me tell you something.

133
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,720
Huo Dongfeng

134
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:31,560
is my big brother.

135
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:36,809
How many scars do you have on your body?

136
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,240
Two, both right here.

137
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:41,400
My brother has three scars.

138
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,159
One of those scars

139
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:44,640
he took for me.

140
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:51,120
That was

141
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,000
in 1979,

142
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:54,760
when I was 18.

143
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,240
I was caught by some guys.

144
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,970
They were going to break my leg.

145
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,920
After my brother found out about this,

146
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:03,280
in the middle of the night,

147
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:05,760
he walked several miles all by himself.

148
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:08,840
Walking all night through ice and snow,

149
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,760
he found me before dawn.

150
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,480
This is my brother.

151
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,560
I'm taking him with me now.

152
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,480
Cut me once,

153
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:34,320
and we'll call it even.

154
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:37,450
Go ahead, cut me.

155
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:40,600
You know who I am, right?

156
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,920
Killing you guys will make me famous.

157
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:48,440
That scar was from taking a hit for me.

158
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:50,200
No wonder.

159
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,440
That's quite a debt to repay.

160
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:56,360
But why did he have to walk?

161
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,600
Couldn't he just ride a bicycle?

162
00:09:58,960 --> 00:09:59,600
He was poor.

163
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,120
Couldn't afford a bicycle back then.

164
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,360
If you're poor, can't you borrow one?

165
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:03,320
It was 1 AM.

166
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,360
Everyone was asleep.

167
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,600
My brother was too proud.

168
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,960
You expect him to knock on doors to borrow one?

169
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:07,600
Back in '79,

170
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,760
people were poor,

171
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:11,090
but every family had at least one bicycle.

172
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:15,020
I'm done talking with you all.

173
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:23,360
Brother,

174
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:24,640
let's go home.

175
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:51,320
Is it a Lada or a Naz?

176
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,000
Crown.

177
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:56,620
Which department did you borrow it from?

178
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,360
It's mine.

179
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:20,840
Wait.

180
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:28,600
Brother.

181
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,060
This car is really stable.

182
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,170
Do you know what car this is?

183
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:47,480
What car?

184
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:48,120
Crown.

185
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:50,890
Brother,

186
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,600
come sit in the front and feel it.

187
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:53,240
I'll move to the back.

188
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:54,240
It's crowded in the back too.

189
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:56,240
No need. I can't move anyway.

190
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:59,200
My fault. I didn't arrange this well.

191
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:00,520
See if he recognizes him.

192
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:01,440
Who's this?

193
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:03,320
Who? He looks familiar.

194
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:05,000
Who is it? I can't remember.

195
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:05,880
Hongwei.

196
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:07,720
Oh my!

197
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:08,480
Hongwei!

198
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:10,000
Wow, it's been so many years!

199
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,000
Oh my goodness.

200
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,480
You came at the perfect time!

201
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:13,720
Perfect timing. I

202
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:14,600
have something to do later.

203
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,000
You take our big brother

204
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,600
to get a haircut and wash first,

205
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:18,520
and I'll arrange everything for tonight.

206
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:19,250
Don't worry.

207
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:19,760
Leave big brother to me.

208
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:20,440
Tonight we'll...

209
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:22,080
go to Dingqing Restaurant.

210
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:23,520
We'll drink till we drop!

211
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,260
Dingqing Restaurant?

212
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,250
Brother, I'm sorry.

213
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:31,200
I forgot.

214
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,400
No, no, no. Not there.

215
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:33,440
Let's go to that place,

216
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:35,680
that seafood restaurant we always went to. What was it called?

217
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:37,400
Is it called Xinji Seafood Restaurant?

218
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:37,840
Yes.

219
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:40,200
Tonight we'll go to Xinji Seafood Restaurant for drinks.

220
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,200
Come with us, Hongwei.

221
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,120
See you tonight.

222
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,180
Sure thing, Ermei.

223
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:58,640
Take this.

224
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:00,720
What's this?

225
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:02,120
Just take it.

226
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:04,000
Is that all?

227
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,520
This money...

228
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,840
Look, it's 100 yuan.

229
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:16,010
I absolutely can't take it.

230
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:16,960
What are you talking about?

231
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:18,490
How could I take your money?

232
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:19,720
Listen, brother.

233
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:21,080
Consider it a loan from me.

234
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,360
Pay me back whenever you earn some money.

235
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,620
No, I can't pay it back.

236
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:25,640
Brother.

237
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:26,360
Big brother.

238
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:28,040
Brother, think about it. Now that you're out,

239
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,500
you're not alone anymore.

240
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:30,880
You're not just a single man.

241
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:32,240
You have a son, right?

242
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:32,920
His name is...

243
00:14:32,920 --> 00:14:33,400
Called...

244
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:34,040
Erpang.

245
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:35,920
Erpang hasn't seen you for so many years.

246
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:37,240
He's suffered so much.

247
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,520
Now that you're out, what are you going to do?

248
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:41,580
Let him continue suffering with you?

249
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:42,200
Now that you're both out,

250
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,400
what will you eat and drink?

251
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:44,530
Where will you live?

252
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:45,560
Listen, brother.

253
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:46,720
You can't just wear these clothes.

254
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:47,960
Go see your son.

255
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:51,050
Alright.

256
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:55,160
I'll pay you back when I earn some money.

257
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:56,930
Hongwei, come here.

258
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:59,920
Let's get Hongwei some new clothes too.

259
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:01,060
Well...

260
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:02,400
Take our brother here

261
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,440
to get a haircut

262
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,700
and then take a shower.

263
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,760
Go to Dongfeng Road to buy two sets of clothes.

264
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:07,520
Get one for yourself too.

265
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:09,320
You go ahead with your business.

266
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:10,120
Alright, let's go.

267
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:11,160
See you tonight, brother.

268
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,240
See you tonight.

269
00:15:15,160 --> 00:15:17,600
This is your hospital deposit refund.

270
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:19,760
6,128 yuan. Please verify it.

271
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:27,620
That'll be 3,000 yuan for the legal fees.

272
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:31,040
Here you go.

273
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:36,560
Based on what you've told me,

274
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:38,160
I understand the situation.

275
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:40,000
But our police

276
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,920
don't just arrest people without reason.

277
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:43,680
Especially in criminal cases like this.

278
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:44,680
It's not a joke.

279
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,240
If they've made an arrest,

280
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:47,640
they must have evidence.

281
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:50,760
No, my friend

282
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:52,680
couldn't possibly have killed anyone.

283
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:54,040
Don't worry.

284
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:55,760
Even if he did commit murder,

285
00:15:56,120 --> 00:15:57,320
we can still find a way

286
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:59,450
to get him a suspended death sentence.

287
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:00,360
No, no.

