Alright. I'll see just how bizarre you can be.

577
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:13,760
Brother,

578
00:32:14,720 --> 00:32:15,560
are you happy?

579
00:32:18,080 --> 00:32:19,010
If you're happy,

580
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:22,000
that's all that matters.

581
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:24,200
I always want the best for you, brother.

582
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:29,440
Pretty good.

583
00:32:32,760 --> 00:32:34,480
We'll split the money I earn.

584
00:32:36,520 --> 00:32:37,440
What for?

585
00:32:38,240 --> 00:32:38,840
Brother,

586
00:32:39,440 --> 00:32:41,120
the money you earn is yours.

587
00:32:41,120 --> 00:32:42,800
You don't need to share with me.

588
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:45,260
As long as you're making money, you're good.

589
00:32:45,800 --> 00:32:47,730
I have plenty of ways to make money.

590
00:32:54,160 --> 00:32:55,520
Debts must be repaid.

591
00:33:02,040 --> 00:33:02,800
Brother.

592
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:05,500
You haven't changed a bit.

593
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:07,440
You'll always be my big brother.

594
00:33:07,440 --> 00:33:08,840
Ladies and gentlemen.

595
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:10,960
Let's give a warm round of applause

596
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:12,320
to welcome the champion

597
00:33:12,320 --> 00:33:14,600
of the city's first karaoke competition.

598
00:33:14,600 --> 00:33:17,720
Cui Guoming!

599
00:34:07,920 --> 00:34:08,520
Brother.

600
00:34:09,239 --> 00:34:10,639
Let's go.

601
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:13,719
What a night.

602
00:34:13,719 --> 00:34:14,719
This is yours,

603
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:16,000
but consider it mine.

604
00:34:18,560 --> 00:34:20,820
How much will we spend on drinks tonight?

605
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:22,280
Don't embarrass yourself.

606
00:34:22,280 --> 00:34:24,440
You can spend as little as a few dozen yuan,

607
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:27,560
or as much as tens of thousands.

608
00:34:31,880 --> 00:34:32,520
Let's go.

609
00:34:35,600 --> 00:34:37,199
Brother, what do you think?

610
00:34:37,199 --> 00:34:38,440
Is it good?

611
00:34:40,679 --> 00:34:41,560
Is it okay?

612
00:34:41,800 --> 00:34:42,320
Come on, brother.

613
00:34:42,320 --> 00:34:43,159
Take it easy.

614
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:46,489
Watch your step.

615
00:34:47,159 --> 00:34:47,690
Brother.

616
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:49,600
Today we'll sit here,

617
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:51,360
in the best spot, okay?

618
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:52,050
Brother.

619
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:57,160
Over here.

620
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:57,690
Brother.

621
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:04,460
Excuse me, sir, could you move aside?

622
00:35:21,320 --> 00:35:22,380
Alright, brother,

623
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:23,440
is this good?

624
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:26,720
That singer

625
00:35:26,720 --> 00:35:28,520
looks a lot like my brother-in-law.

626
00:35:28,520 --> 00:35:29,360
Really?

627
00:35:30,240 --> 00:35:31,520
Bring that flower basket

628
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:32,560
over there.

629
00:35:34,160 --> 00:35:35,220
Bring the flowers.

630
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:36,840
Hurry up!

631
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:52,970
Thank you, brother.

632
00:36:03,240 --> 00:36:04,370
Thank you, brother.

633
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:09,320
He is my brother-in-law.

634
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:18,440
Why are these flowers being sent?

635
00:36:19,160 --> 00:36:20,360
Don't worry about it, brother.

636
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:21,120
Go all out!

637
00:36:21,200 --> 00:36:21,960
Bring the big flower basket,

638
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:22,890
the biggest one!

639
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:26,420
Bring the flowers,

640
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:27,800
give a tip!

641
00:36:37,720 --> 00:36:38,600
Look at this,

642
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:39,680
what do you think?

643
00:36:57,400 --> 00:36:58,680
It's fine.

644
00:37:01,520 --> 00:37:02,320
Brother.

645
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:03,000
Brother-in-law?

646
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:04,760
Why does your brother-in-law call you 'brother'?

647
00:37:04,760 --> 00:37:07,160
Instead of calling you 'brother-in-law'?

648
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:11,450
That's a good question.

649
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:14,290
Do you have an answer to that question?

650
00:37:15,960 --> 00:37:16,720
No answer.

651
00:37:16,720 --> 00:37:19,250
Would it be a good question if it had an answer?

652
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:22,480
Come on, brother.

653
00:37:25,920 --> 00:37:27,240
You just got out

654
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:31,720
and you're making such a big show. Impressive.

655
00:37:33,520 --> 00:37:34,850
My friends give me face.

656
00:37:35,480 --> 00:37:36,520
I told Er Pang

657
00:37:36,520 --> 00:37:38,650
that I'd treat you to dinner tomorrow.

658
00:37:39,320 --> 00:37:40,000
Didn't expect today.

659
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,200
The one sitting next to you,

660
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:42,400
that's Er Mei, right?

661
00:37:42,840 --> 00:37:44,120
Yes, it's Er Mei. Why?

662
00:37:53,640 --> 00:37:54,480
Well,

663
00:37:55,160 --> 00:37:56,080
you two.

664
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:58,040
You're now the most

665
00:37:58,760 --> 00:38:00,760
popular stars in our Liudao Street.

666
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:03,240
AC Milan has their Three Musketeers,

667
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:05,240
and you two together are

668
00:38:05,240 --> 00:38:07,760
the Twin Stars of Liudao Street.

669
00:38:08,160 --> 00:38:09,960
With you, we'd be the Three Musketeers.

670
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:11,160
No, please, brother.

671
00:38:11,160 --> 00:38:12,120
Give me a break.

672
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:15,800
Look, you just got out

673
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:17,360
and if you don't hang out with Erpang

674
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:18,880
but stay with Ermei instead,

675
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:19,840
I can basically see

676
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:21,040
your future already.

677
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:23,080
I just had a meal with Ermei,

678
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:25,200
and you think you've figured out my entire life?

679
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:26,930
Should I just stop living then?

680
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:27,880
Well...

681
00:38:31,760 --> 00:38:32,960
Ermei is now

682
00:38:33,280 --> 00:38:34,320
quite famous.

683
00:38:34,960 --> 00:38:36,760
Not just people at work know him,

684
00:38:36,760 --> 00:38:38,400
even schoolkids fighting mention his name.

685
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:39,760
All my relatives,

686
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:41,400
everyone knows Ermei.

687
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:42,730
Isn't that impressive?

688
00:38:43,840 --> 00:38:44,240
What?

689
00:38:44,240 --> 00:38:45,480
You're telling me all this

690
00:38:45,480 --> 00:38:47,320
to say I'm not good enough anymore?

691
00:38:47,320 --> 00:38:48,650
That's not what I meant.

692
00:38:49,240 --> 00:38:51,570
I heard everything from Hongwei already.

693
00:38:51,600 --> 00:38:52,400
Have you noticed

694
00:38:52,400 --> 00:38:54,200
his clothes are always bulging?

695
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:55,960
I know he's rich now.

696
00:38:58,760 --> 00:39:00,620
He's wearing a bulletproof vest.

697
00:39:01,680 --> 00:39:03,600
Don't talk nonsense. Is that necessary?

698
00:39:03,600 --> 00:39:05,160
What? Aren't you scared, bro?

699
00:39:05,160 --> 00:39:06,220
What am I afraid of?

700
00:39:06,880 --> 00:39:08,960
Isn't that how everyone survives out there?

701
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:11,620
Who wears a bulletproof vest just to get by, bro?

702
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:16,680
Look at how you guys used to be.

703
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:18,400
Getting beaten black and blue,

704
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:19,760
selling watches and cars,

705
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:21,200
then paying medical bills,

706
00:39:21,200 --> 00:39:22,400
then going out drinking again.

707
00:39:22,400 --> 00:39:24,240
That's what I call struggling when you're poor.

708
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:25,440
Not much damage done.

709
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:26,840
Things are different now.

710
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:28,360
This guy's even wearing a bulletproof vest.

711
00:39:28,360 --> 00:39:30,880
Look at him spending money like water,

712
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:32,320
throwing it around.

713
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:33,360
He just doesn't know

714
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:35,000
when his time will be up.

715
00:39:35,720 --> 00:39:36,360
This is

716
00:39:36,840 --> 00:39:38,440
playing with his life.

717
00:39:39,600 --> 00:39:41,460
Er Mei suffered since childhood.

718
00:39:43,040 --> 00:39:44,170
His family was poor.

719
00:39:45,600 --> 00:39:46,600
But he's got high ambitions.

720
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:48,320
If he doesn't risk his life,

721
00:39:48,320 --> 00:39:49,200
what else can he use to get ahead?

722
00:39:49,200 --> 00:39:50,320
Why are you making excuses for him?

723
00:39:50,320 --> 00:39:51,800
Everyone's poor. Everyone struggles.

724
00:39:51,800 --> 00:39:53,200
Does he have to hang out with those gangsters?

725
00:39:53,200 --> 00:39:54,800
Just promise me

726
00:39:55,200 --> 00:39:57,460
you'll stop hanging out with them, okay?

727
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,080
I'm not hanging out with him.

728
00:40:01,080 --> 00:40:01,760
Who am I hanging out with?

729
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:03,160
I'm hanging out with you.

730
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:05,880
But your thing,

731
00:40:06,640 --> 00:40:07,600
your job,

732
00:40:07,920 --> 00:40:09,200
I can't do what you do.

733
00:40:09,200 --> 00:40:10,000
Your thing...

734
00:40:10,200 --> 00:40:11,200
What's wrong with what I do?

735
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:12,360
Am I just hanging around?

736
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:13,640
Is what I do anything like what you guys do?

737
00:40:13,640 --> 00:40:14,200
I'm earning money.

738
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:15,660
I'm supporting my family.

739
00:40:16,720 --> 00:40:17,800
Can you promise me

740
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:19,130
not to hang out with him?

741
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:20,480
I promise you.

742
00:40:20,480 --> 00:40:22,160
I won't hang out with Ermei.

743
00:40:22,720 --> 00:40:23,520
I believe you.

744
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:27,060
Let's talk about something serious.

745
00:40:27,160 --> 00:40:29,360
What do you want to do next?

746
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:30,880
Ermei found me a job.

747
00:40:37,080 --> 00:40:39,360
You're being disrespectful, bro.

748
00:40:39,360 --> 00:40:40,880
I've been drinking with you all night,

749
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:41,880
and you're messing with me?

750
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:42,600
After all these years,

751
00:40:42,600 --> 00:40:43,760
I haven't been this happy.

752
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:45,040
First I think of Erpang,

753
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:45,920
and then I think of you.

754
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:46,480
That's enough.

755
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:47,440
You're making fun of me.

756
00:40:47,440 --> 00:40:49,160
No, no, no.

757
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:51,760
He found me a job selling fish.

758
00:40:52,760 --> 00:40:53,760
At the fish market.

759
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:55,320
Is it really just selling fish?

760
00:40:55,320 --> 00:40:56,980
I'll be working with Hongwei.

761
00:40:57,720 --> 00:40:59,520
Okay, wait.

762
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:01,560
Let me ask you one more question.

763
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:03,600
You're known for being loyal.

764
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:05,640
Very loyal. After you got out,

765
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:07,600
Ermei gave you such a grand welcome

766
00:41:07,600 --> 00:41:09,040
and even found you a job.

767
00:41:09,040 --> 00:41:10,880
If one day he gets into a fight,

768
00:41:10,880 --> 00:41:12,480
I'm asking if you'll join in.

769
00:41:13,080 --> 00:41:14,000
Of course I will.

770
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:15,200
Then everything I said tonight

771
00:41:15,200 --> 00:41:16,400
was a complete waste.

772
00:41:17,160 --> 00:41:18,020
That's enough.

773
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:19,080
Check, please.

774
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:20,200
Wait, wait.

775
00:41:22,960 --> 00:41:24,220
I'll definitely join.

776
00:41:24,440 --> 00:41:25,280
Boss, hurry up with the bill.

777
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:27,080
Hold on. That's not what I meant.

778
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:28,200
What do you mean?

779
00:41:28,200 --> 00:41:30,440
There's one thing I'm certain of.

780
00:41:30,440 --> 00:41:31,720
What can you be sure of?

781
00:41:31,720 --> 00:41:32,760
If you hang out with him,

782
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:34,280
can you be sure you won't break the law?

783
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:36,120
Or can you be sure you'll survive?

784
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:37,240
I'm certain that

785
00:41:38,640 --> 00:41:39,920
for something as serious as murder,

786
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:41,050
he wouldn't call me.

787
00:41:41,120 --> 00:41:42,760
How can you be so sure?

788
00:41:42,760 --> 00:41:44,880
I'm certain he won't call me.

789
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:46,080
I swear on this light.

790
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:48,400
Look at it.

791
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:49,320
Even the light doesn't believe you.

792
00:41:49,320 --> 00:41:50,320
It went out, bro.

793
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:50,880
It's on.

794
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:53,120
See? It didn't go out.

795
00:41:53,760 --> 00:41:54,600
I'm telling you.

796
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:55,600
I'm absolutely certain.

797
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:57,200
You're drunk out of your mind, bro.

798
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:58,800
I'm asking you for one thing.

799
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:00,280
Bro, now that you're out,

800
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:03,800
can you stay longer this time?

801
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:06,040
Erpang, this kid,

802
00:42:06,560 --> 00:42:07,680
he's always wanted

803
00:42:07,680 --> 00:42:09,200
a real family.

804
00:42:09,680 --> 00:42:11,560
I hope this time you're out,

805
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:13,650
you'll take care of this first.

806
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:17,600
His uncle.

807
00:42:19,320 --> 00:42:20,680
Thank you for your hard work.

808
00:42:20,680 --> 00:42:21,920
It really is.

809
00:42:22,880 --> 00:42:25,040
If you'd stay away from that bulletproof vest,

810
00:42:25,040 --> 00:42:26,770
I wouldn't have to work so hard.

811
00:42:44,040 --> 00:42:44,770
Pretty good.

812
00:42:46,240 --> 00:42:46,720
Bro.

813
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:47,880
How is it?

814
00:42:51,760 --> 00:42:53,280
The flavor is quite rich.

815
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:54,200
Of course it is.

816
00:42:54,200 --> 00:42:56,000
That's how a fish market should smell.
